node.text:
@titlemtb is live and our components are available online for purchase now.
.
I didn’t plan on being the guy behind the brand but I guess that’s just how it turned out. Thank you to so many people for helping this come to life; athletes, factories, machinists, filmmakers, photographers, artists, writers, designers, family and friends. It’s been fun building a brand, but challenging to say the least and my hat goes off to all other companies that have built themselves from the ground up.
.
Excited to see where we can take this 🙌🏼.
.
Director: @harrisonmendel
Cinematography: @harrisonmendel, @liammullany, @clayporter, @simonberggren, @davidpeacockfilm 
Editing: @davidpeacockfilm, @harrisonmendel 
Scored by: @andrewjudah
Colour: Sam Gilling
Sound Design + Mix: @j_chiodo 
Titles: @studiodialog

Now available for digital download on all major media platforms. Link is in my bio. In collaboration with @harrisonmendel, we go in depth behind the scenes and show quite a lot that I haven’t been comfortable with showing in the past. You’ll see and learn lots about my contest life, who is involved, what is involved and the ups and downs that I went through in 2018. Stoked to call this my second major film project that I’ve produced. Enjoy 🙏🏻.

node.text:
I took this photo one hour before sunset last night on my drive home from Revelstoke. My throat burning, eyes stinging, heart heavy.

I’ve been quiet for a while. Probably so quiet you don’t know where I went. Truth is I’m finding it difficult to be the person you all know me as again after educating myself about the state of our planet and climate change. A cork 720 barspin and a double flip 3 no longer seem relevant to me. I’ve been unable to put words to my content because everything I do seems to go against what we (as humans) need to do to make sure we can live on the planet for the next 80 years and more.

Im living, breathing and seeing the result of climate change in my hometown, Vernon, BC. My home has been on evacuation alert two times this year, I sweep ash off my doorstep and keep sprinklers on my roof.

Yesterday I listened to a podcast about the UN climate report “code red for humanity”. The report basically says that once the planet becomes climate neutral it will still take 30 years of worsening conditions before things get better. This means that what we’re experiencing this summer (drought, wildfires, floods) will only get worse. For the next 30 years. Even after we change. This is heavy news. Hard to brush off. It changes everything.

Had a few days away from filming and decided to race all three Canada Cups in the #dunbarsummerseries. It was again refreshing participating in something so different from what I normally do. The race community in BC is amazing. I had pretty solid race runs in Fernie and Panorama but washed out on the last corner at Nationals in Kicking Horse😵. Amazing learning experience to say the least! Stoked for more, but back to filming for now.

node.text:
TITLE LINE | SilverStar Bike Park | Est. 2021

I wanted to give back to the sport and community that has given me so much. So I assembled a dream crew and we built a two-part trail that riders of all different skill levels can ride, enjoy and push themselves on in the safest way possible. 

From us to you, please enjoy the Title Line at SilverStar Bike Park. 

@titlemtb #TitleLine #TitleMTB #silverstarbikepark #bermsandberms #highwayman #everythingissick 

Photo | @beardofbeez
